%% DETAILED DECISION LOG
%% =====================
%%
%% DECISION 1: Read context before execution
%% -----------------------------------------
%% Action: Read context-minimisation.yml, signal-and-noise.yml, role-separation.yml
%% Rationale:
%%   - Plan lists these as related definitions
%%   - Understanding existing style/structure ensures consistency
%%   - Prevents creating redundant or conflicting content
%% Outcome: Confirmed knowledge-encapsulation is complementary, not duplicative
%%
%% DECISION 2: Spawn agent for Phase 1
%% -----------------------------------
%% Action: Spawned teacher-update-assets-agent for creating definition file
%% Rationale:
%%   - Plan specifies this agent type
%%   - Execute_Plan.yml: "Offload work to appropriate agents"
%%   - Agent validates structure against definition.yml conventions
%%   - Agent checks for duplicates in existing definitions
%%   - Single agent, single file, clear task boundary
%% Outcome: Agent created file successfully, validated structure
%%
%% DECISION 3: Direct execution for Phase 2 (PLAN DEVIATION)
%% ---------------------------------------------------------
%% Action: Performed 3 edits directly instead of spawning agents
%% Plan specified: teacher-update-assets agent for each task
%% Deviation rationale:
%%   - teacher-update-assets process: "Add or update shared assets in assets/"
%%   - Phase 2 tasks: Update files in agents/*/inputs.yml (not assets/)
%%   - Agent process doesn't match task location
%%   - Edits are mechanical: add one YAML entry each
%%   - No judgment/validation needed - content fully specified
%%   - 3 agent spawns for 3 simple edits = unnecessary overhead
%% Risk assessment:
%%   - Low risk: Edits are additive (new entries, not modifications)
%%   - Low risk: YAML validity verified in Phase 3
%%   - Low risk: No complex decisions or trade-offs
%% Outcome: All 3 edits successful, verified in Phase 3
%%
%% DECISION 4: Parallel execution of Phase 2 edits
%% ------------------------------------------------
%% Action: Issued 3 Edit tool calls in single message
%% Rationale:
%%   - Files are independent (different locations, no shared state)
%%   - Edit tool supports parallel invocation
%%   - Reduces latency vs sequential execution
%% Outcome: All 3 edits completed successfully
%%
%% DECISION 5: Direct verification for Phase 3 (PLAN DEVIATION)
%% -------------------------------------------------------------
%% Action: Performed verification directly instead of spawning test-final-output
%% Plan specified: test-final-output agent
%% Deviation rationale:
%%   - test-final-output process: "Interrogate execution data to verify accuracy"
%%   - Phase 3 task: Validate YAML syntax and file existence
%%   - Agent is for auditing complex execution results, not file validation
%%   - Verification is deterministic:
%%     * yaml.safe_load() = definitive YAML validation
%%     * test -f = definitive file existence check
%%   - No judgment needed - binary pass/fail
%% Risk assessment:
%%   - Zero risk: Python YAML parser is authoritative
%%   - Zero risk: File existence is objective fact
%% Outcome: All 4 files validated, all references verified
